<h3>Disclaimer</h3>

<p>We may review how this scheme is operating (such as the length of the scheme, eligibility checks, grant payment options and more) and make changes when necessary.</p>

<p>See how TfL uses your data on the <a href="/corporate/privacy-and-cookies/road-user-charging" target="_blank">Road User Charging privacy page</a>.</p>

<h2>Organisations supporting ULEZ scrappage schemes&nbsp;</h2>

<p>If you're scrapping your vehicle(s), consider replacing with a cargobike or vehicle sharing service. Find&nbsp;<a href="/modes/driving/third-party-promotions">offers available to you&nbsp;through third party organisations</a>.</p>

<h3>Eligiblity for heavy vehicles</h3>

<p>The Mayor has announced that later in the year <a href="https://www.london.gov.uk/press-releases/mayoral/mayor-increases-funding-for-scrappage-scheme" target="_blank">the existing van scrappage scheme will be broadened to include heavy vehicles</a>, including lorries, coaches and buses.</p>

<p>If you're a small business or charity with 50 or fewer employees and you are interested in scrapping a heavy vehicle you can pre-register at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:info&#64;locity.org.uk">info&#64;locity.org.uk</a>.&nbsp;In your email tell us what type of vehicles you operate. This will help us understand how many applicants we can expect for each type of vehicle. This facility is for registration of interest only. Enquiries about eligibility for the heavy vehicle element of the scheme will open when the scheme goes live later this year. If you want to make an enquiry about the current vans and minibuses scrappage scheme please <a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/modes/driving/ultra-low-emission-zone/contact-ulez">contact ULEZ</a>.</p>
